## Files

- `train.py` -- The ONLY file you modify. Contains model architecture,
  optimizer, hyperparameters, and training loop.
- `prepare.py` -- read-only. Contains fixed evaluation metric, data loading,
  tokenizer, and constants.

`train.py` imports from `prepare.py`:

    from prepare import MAX_SEQ_LEN, TIME_BUDGET, Tokenizer, make_dataloader, evaluate_bpb

## Constraints

- You may ONLY modify `train.py`.
- The script must run on GPU. Do not change the device to CPU, CUDA setup, GPU
  memory config, or autocast context.
- Do not change the evaluation harness, time budget, validation configuration,
  or output format.
- Do not introduce information leakage from future tokens.
- Keep VRAM growth controlled; if model size grows meaningfully, reduce batch
  size or gradient accumulation to stay within memory.
- Simpler code is better, all else being equal.

